<title>CANADA: Nestle buys Ault arm for C$221 mln.</title>
<headline>Nestle buys Ault arm for C$221 mln.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1996-12-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ault Foods Ltd said it agreed to sell its frozen products division to Nestle Canada Inc., a unit of Nestle SA, for C$221 million.</p>
<p>Toronto-based Ault said it intends to use some of the money to retire indebtedness and expects to distribute more than C$100 million to shareholders, probably through a share repurchase in early 1997.  </p>
<p>Food producer Nestle Canada will acquire Ault's ice cream and frozen novelty food plant, warehouses, distribution centres and some frozen product trademarks along with long-term suppy and co-pack agreements.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8109))</p>
